    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-09-11T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-09-11T16:00:00-05:00" n="747"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d747">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2689: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-09-11T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 11, 1922—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>218. Legation’s 365 of September 8, 5 p.m. Immediately after the Washington
                    Conference China was invited in a most friendly manner to consider the problem
                    of the Chinese Eastern, but she seemed to show no disposition toward
                    international cooperation. At your discretion you may point this out to the
                    Minister for Foreign Affairs, referring to our telegrams 22 of February 3, 7
                        p.m.,<note n="87" xml:id="d747fn87">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_882">p. 882</ref>.</note> and
                    52 of March 7, 4 p.m.,<note n="88" xml:id="d747fn88">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_888">p. 888</ref>.</note> and
                    to the Legation’s telegrams 89 of March 8,<note n="89" xml:id="d747fn89">Not
                        printed.</note> and 118 of March 25, 1 p.m.<note n="90" xml:id="d747fn90">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_889">p. 889</ref>.</note> The
                    other Powers are interchanging views at present. In due time communication will
                    be made to the Chinese Government.</p>
                <p>The Embassy in Japan has doubtless advised you regarding the nature of the
                    proposed action. When answers have been received from France and Italy you will
                    be completely informed. Concurrence has already been received from the British
                    and Japanese Governments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
